<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1129,1542]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">
A male specimen was designated as the 
<typeStatus box="[631,734,1129,1155]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">holotype</typeStatus>
by Sonan (
<number box="[872,936,1129,1155]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" value="1936.0">1936</number>
), and this 
<typeStatus box="[1059,1162,1129,1155]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">holotype</typeStatus>
was retrieved in 
<collectionCode box="[1369,1435,1129,1155]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/a13e-ta1z" name="Taiwan Agricultural Research Institute" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">TARI</collectionCode>
(
<figureCitation box="[160,304,1168,1194]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 18" captionStartId="2.[151,273,1746,1770]" captionTargetBox="[204,1392,187,1723]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[183,1411,179,1723]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 18. Types of skipper taxa described by Jinhaku Sonan: 1 – 3, holotype of Lobocla kodairai, upperside, underside, labels; 4 – 6, holotype of Coladenia sadakoe, upperside, underside, labels; 7 – 9, holotype of Tagiades menaka kotoshona, upperside, underside, labels; 10 – 12, holotype of Notocrypta arisana, upperside, underside, labels; 13 – 15, holotype of Ampittia maro matsumurai, upperside, underside, labels; 16 – 18. holotype of Augiades bouddha niitakana, upperside, underside, labels." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/189655/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">
Fig. 
<number box="[220,304,1168,1194]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" value="17.0" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="16.0">16–18</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[327,495,1168,1194]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" refString="Evans, W. H. (1949) A catalogue of the Hesperiidae from Europe, Asia and Australia in the British Museum (Natural History). The British Museum (Natural History), London, xix + 502 pp." type="book" year="1949">
Evans (
<number box="[421,487,1168,1194]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" value="1949.0">1949</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
treated this taxon as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authority="Moore, 1878" authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1878" box="[970,1322,1168,1194]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ochlodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="siva">
<emphasis box="[970,1148,1168,1193]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">Ochlodes siva</emphasis>
Moore, 
<number box="[1257,1322,1168,1194]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" value="1878.0">1878</number>
</taxonomicName>
, and this treatment was followed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bridges" box="[484,671,1206,1232]" pageId="5" pageNumber="57" refString="Bridges, C. A. (1983) Lepidoptera: Hesperiidae, Notes on Species-Group Names. Published by author, Urbana, 274 pp." type="book" year="1983">
Bridges (
<number box="[596,662,1206,1232]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" value="1983.0">1983</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Shirozu" box="[683,870,1206,1232]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" refString="Shirozu, T. (1960) Butterflies of Formosa in Colour. Hoikusha, Osaka, 481 pp. [In Japanese]" type="book" year="1960">
Shirôzu (
<number box="[795,860,1206,1232]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" value="1960.0">1960</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, however, considered this taxon a synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,368,1245,1270]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Augiades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sylvanus">
<emphasis box="[151,368,1245,1270]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">Augiades sylvanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName authority="Matsumura, 1919" authorityName="Matsumura" authorityYear="1919" box="[375,767,1245,1271]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" rank="variety" variety="formosana">
var. 
<emphasis box="[426,551,1245,1270]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">formosana</emphasis>
Matsumura, 
<number box="[706,767,1245,1271]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" value="1919.0">1919</number>
</taxonomicName>
, which was recognized to represent a valid subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authority="Bremer &amp; Grey, 1853" authorityName="Bremer &amp; Grey" authorityYear="1853" box="[151,680,1284,1310]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ochlodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subhyalina">
<emphasis box="[151,398,1284,1309]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">Ochlodes subhyalina</emphasis>
(Bremer &amp; Grey, 
<number box="[612,672,1284,1310]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" value="1853.0">1853</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[725,886,1284,1310]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" refString="Evans, W. H. (1949) A catalogue of the Hesperiidae from Europe, Asia and Australia in the British Museum (Natural History). The British Museum (Natural History), London, xix + 502 pp." type="book" year="1949">
Evans (
<number box="[813,877,1284,1310]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" value="1949.0">1949</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Based on the characteristics of male genitalia, 
<bibRefCitation author="Chiba" box="[151,504,1322,1348]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="58" pageId="5" pageNumber="57" refString="Chiba, H &amp; Tsukiyama, H. (1996) A review of the genus Ochlodes Scudder, 1872, with special reference to the Eurasian species (Lepidoptera: Hesperiidae). Butterflies, 14, 3 - 16. [In Japanese with English abstract]" type="journal article" year="1996">
Chiba and Tsukiyama (
<number box="[432,495,1322,1348]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" value="1996.0">1996</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
subsequently raised 
<emphasis box="[759,888,1323,1348]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">formosana</emphasis>
to species status, and considered it a species endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[291,382,1361,1387]" name="Taiwan" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation box="[393,600,1361,1387]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" refString="Hsu, Y. F., Chiba, H., Yang, Y. C., Tsukiyama, H., Yang, P. S. &amp; Wang S. M. (2006) A Taxonomic review of the Taiwanese skippers described by Shonen Matsumura (Lepidoptera: Hesperiidae). Zoological Studies, 45, 322 - 338." type="journal article">
Hsu 
<emphasis box="[449,510,1361,1386]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[527,592,1361,1387]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" value="2006.0">2006</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, however, found that 
<emphasis box="[860,987,1361,1386]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">formosana</emphasis>
Matsumura, 
<number box="[1146,1205,1361,1387]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" value="1919.0">1919</number>
is actually a junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Bremer &amp; Grey, 1853" authorityName="Bremer &amp; Grey" authorityYear="1853" box="[447,967,1400,1426]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ochlodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venata">
<emphasis box="[447,658,1400,1425]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">Ochlodes venata</emphasis>
(Bremer &amp; Grey, 
<number box="[891,958,1400,1426]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" value="1853.0">1853</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
, so 
<emphasis box="[1019,1138,1400,1425]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">niitakana</emphasis>
Sonan, 
<number box="[1243,1305,1400,1426]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" value="1936.0">1936</number>
should be resurrected in the combination 
<taxonomicName box="[538,791,1439,1464]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ochlodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niitakanus">
<emphasis box="[538,791,1439,1464]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">Ochlodes niitakanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Shirozu" box="[808,994,1438,1464]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" refString="Shirozu, T. (1960) Butterflies of Formosa in Colour. Hoikusha, Osaka, 481 pp. [In Japanese]" type="book" year="1960">
Shirôzu (
<number box="[921,985,1438,1464]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" value="1960.0">1960</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
claimed that the allotype female of 
<emphasis box="[151,264,1477,1502]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">niitakana</emphasis>
was probably a different species. His statement seems to be groundless. We examined the female 
<typeStatus box="[151,252,1516,1542]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">paratype</typeStatus>
of 
<emphasis box="[291,402,1516,1541]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">niitakana</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[417,547,1516,1542]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 39" captionStartId="4.[151,270,1872,1896]" captionTargetBox="[192,1389,202,1833]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1401,197,1835]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 39. Types of skipper taxa described by Jinhaku Sonan: 19 – 21, paratype of Augiades bouddha niitakana, upperside, underside, labels; 22 – 24, holotype of Parnara kotoshona, upperside, underside, labels; 25 – 27, holotype of Parnara ranrunna, upperside, underside, labels; 28 – 30, holotype of Pamara kiraizana, upperside, underside, labels; 31 – 33, holotype of Gangara thyrsis hainana, upperside, underside, labels; 34 – 36, holotype of Telicota palmarum hainanum, upperside, upperside, labels; 37 – 39, holotype of Tagiades menaka hainana, upperside, underside, labels." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/189656/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">
Fig. 
<number box="[472,547,1516,1542]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53" value="20.0" valueMax="21.0" valueMin="19.0">19–21</number>
</figureCitation>
) and confirmed that it was conspecific with the male 
<typeStatus box="[1175,1281,1516,1542]" pageId="5" pageNumber="53">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
